As in the previous case (Part 2), each client should receive every chunk on a separate connection.

Submission guidelines:
Sign and attach the self-work form. Form is here.
The submission directory should have following structure,
   
     rollno-lab8/
                |_ part1
		  |_ readme        (usage commands to execute client and server)
		  |_ outputs       (sample runs, show at least three runs and corresponding outputs)
		|_ part2
		  |_ readme        (usage commands to execute client and server)
		  |_ outputs       (sample runs, show at least three runs and corresponding outputs)
		|_ part3
		  |_ readme        (usage commands to execute client and server)
		  |_ outputs       (sample runs, show at least three runs and corresponding outputs)

Executing each of the task scripts should generate the associated/correct output. 
Required data files, if any, should in the correct directories or specified via path names as part of command-line arguments. 
If the above commands fail to generate your answers, submission will be treated incomplete.
Create a tar.gz file of your submission. The archive should contain the main directory and all sub-directories. 
Name the tar archive yourrollno-lab7.tar.gz. 
Read up the man page for tar.
Upload the tar.gz file on the moodle site for the course.
submission deadlines: 
      very early deadline: 23/3/12, 4.55 p.m. (max marks: 24) 
